The paper deals with text line segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision and natural language processing. The method proposed in the paper is based on unsupervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also involves text processing and feature extraction, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
